git config --list 
    lists all the current configurations

git config <key>
    gives value of key config eg. git config user.name

git config --global <key> <value>
    sets value of key in global config

cofig can be stored at three levels - system, global, current git repository
eg: git config --system user.name, git config --global user.name, git config user.name gives user names in system, global and local repo respectively